-- FACTBOX-Key facts about Deutsche Telekom and Sprint Nextel
-- 
-- Mon Sep 14, 2009 12:47pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2009/09/14/us-deutschetelekom-sprintnextel-sb-idUSTRE58D40920090914

 

 (Reuters) - Shares in Sprint Nextel soared on Monday, boosted by a newspaper report that Deutsche Telekom was mulling a bid for the U.S. mobile operator. 

 Following are key facts about Deutsche Telekom and Sprint Nextel: DEUTSCHE TELEKOM: * KEY DATA (Three months to June 30 Revenue: 16,238 million euros Net profit: 521 million euros Total Assets: 132,902 million euros Cash & Equivalents: 5,836 million euros * OPERATIONS Number of fixed network lines: 39.6 million Number of broadband lines: 17.2 million Number of Mobile customers: 149.8 million Employees: 260,000 * RECENT EVENTS -- Deutsche Telekom last week agreed a deal with France Telecom to combine their British mobile phone businesses T-Mobile and Orange to create Britain's leading mobile operator with a combined customer base of 28.4 million. -- The Bonn-based company said in April it planned to combine its German fixed-line and wireless units into a single division to save costs. SPRINT NEXTEL: * KEY DATA (Three months to June 30) Revenue $8,141 million Net loss $384 million Total Assets $55,885 million Cash & Equivalents $4,592 million * OPERATIONS Wireless customers 48.8 million Employees 56,000 * RECENT EVENTS -- The No. 3 U.S. mobile service provider said in January it was cutting up to 8,000 jobs, or about 14 percent of its workforce, as part of a plan to reduce annual labor costs by $1.2 billion. -- Last October, Sprint announced plans to retain its customer-losing iDen network after efforts to sell it failed. Sources: Reuters; www.sprint.com; www.deutschetelekom.com (Writing by Jijo Jacob, Bangalore Editorial Reference Unit; Editing by Dan Lalor)